The paper deals with video understanding and temporal action localization, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new diagnostic tool to analyze the performance of temporal action detectors, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper analyzes the performance of different methods in the latest ActivityNet action localization challenge, which involves multimedia analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses strategies to reduce localization errors, which involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR).
